data.value:
Linuxide's original aim is to install a Linux distribution from Windows without the use any of storage medium or network installers, but it remains a simple Linux image flasher onto the hard drive. Now, before you start wondering "uNetBootin has it, why make a seperate tool?", my goal is to simplifiy the process of flashing a linux image to a system partition simplified, and similar to Windows' Media Creation Tool application, that can later be independent from utilities like diskpart. Just to be clear, i am not offensive to uNetBootin, i appreciate the guys working on the application.
Before you start please see below:
1. I am not responsible for any damage/data loss to your hardware/software in any kind. 2. Your main system partition is going to be shrinked by 6 gigabytes. 3. Only UEFI is supported (neither legacy/bios nor UEFI-CSM). 4. Don't provide dd-only images to Linuxide (e.g Manjaro). 5. There is no gurantee that all distributions are going to work. 6. Fun-fact: You can flash Windows images as well! (Windows 8 or greater, but why do it?)
